    subtitle="Running into a problem? Here are the most common IPTV Smarters Pro Firestick issues and how to fix them instantly."
    columns={2}
    items={[
      {
        title: 'Buffering or Freezing',
        description:
          'Make sure your Wi-Fi speed is at least 10 Mbps for HD and 25 Mbps for 4K. Restart your router, move your Firestick closer to the router, or switch to a 5GHz Wi-Fi band. IPTV Smarters PRO servers use anti-freeze technology but a slow home network can still cause buffering.',
        icon: 'tabler:wifi',
      },
      {
        title: 'App Not Installing (APK Blocked)',
        description:
          'Go back to Settings → My Fire TV → Developer Options and confirm "Apps from Unknown Sources" is enabled. If prompted with a security warning during install, tap "Install Anyway". This is normal when sideloading any APK on Firestick.',
        icon: 'tabler:shield-x',
      },
      {
        title: 'Invalid Credentials / Cannot Connect',
        description:
          'Double-check the Server URL, Username, and Password sent in your IPTV Smarters PRO welcome email — copy and paste them rather than typing manually. Make sure you have an active subscription. Contact our 24/7 support on WhatsApp or Telegram for instant help.',
        icon: 'tabler:key',
      },
      {
        title: 'IPTV Smarters Pro Crashing on Firestick',
        description:
          'Clear the app cache: Settings → Applications → Manage Installed Applications → IPTV Smarters Pro → Clear Cache. If the issue persists, uninstall and reinstall the latest APK version. Older Firestick models (1st gen) may need a lighter IPTV player like GSE IPTV instead.',
        icon: 'tabler:refresh',
      },
      {
        title: 'No Channels Loading After Login',
        description:
          'Your playlist may still be loading for the first time — wait 60–90 seconds for a large channel list to parse. If channels still do not appear, your M3U URL or Xtream Codes credentials may have changed. Log out, re-enter your credentials, or contact IPTV Smarters PRO support.',
        icon: 'tabler:list',
      },
      {
        title: 'EPG / TV Guide Not Showing',
        description:
          'In IPTV Smarters Pro go to Settings → EPG Settings and make sure your EPG URL is filled in (your IPTV Smarters PRO credentials include EPG automatically). Force a manual EPG refresh. EPG data can take 2–5 minutes to fully load after a fresh install.',
        icon: 'tabler:calendar',
      },
    ]}
  />

