          'No jailbreak is needed. Amazon Firestick natively supports sideloading via the Developer Options menu. This is completely different from jailbreaking — it is an official Amazon feature that millions of users use safely every day.',
      },
      {
        title: 'What internet speed do I need for IPTV Smarters Pro on Firestick?',
        description:
          'For SD quality: 5 Mbps minimum. For Full HD: 10 Mbps. For 4K Ultra HD: 25 Mbps. For multiple simultaneous streams: add 10–25 Mbps per additional stream. We recommend a 5GHz Wi-Fi connection or an Ethernet adapter for the most stable IPTV Smarters Pro experience on Firestick.',
      },
      {
        title: 'How many devices can I use with one IPTV Smarters PRO subscription?',
        description:
          'Each IPTV Smarters PRO plan supports up to 3 simultaneous connections by default. You can install IPTV Smarters Pro on as many devices as you like (Firestick, Android, iOS, Smart TV, etc.) but only 3 streams can play at the same time. Multi-connection plans are also available.',
      },
      {
        title: 'What is the difference between M3U and Xtream Codes login in IPTV Smarters Pro?',
        description:
          'Both methods connect your IPTV Smarters PRO subscription to the app. Xtream Codes API (Server URL + Username + Password) is the recommended method — it is faster, supports EPG automatically, and allows VOD/Catch-up TV. M3U URL is a simpler playlist format that works but has fewer features. IPTV Smarters PRO provides both options.',
      },
    ]}
  />

